cs.CR, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.DB, cs.CY 

This paper discusses privacy-preserving and robust collaborative filtering recommenders, which involves topics related to security (cs.CR), information retrieval (cs.IR), machine learning (cs.LG), databases (cs.DB), and cybernetics (cs.CY). The paper proposes a new security model and cryptographic protocols for privacy-preserving prediction computing, which falls under the scope of cs.CR. The use of latent factor based collaborative filtering recommenders and model training also relates to cs.IR and cs.LG. Additionally, the paper discusses the privacy concerns of end users, which is relevant to cs.DB and cs.CY.
